# AUTOSAR Coding Standard Rule

This rule applies to all code work in this repository.

Source of truth:

- `Autosar_SecOC/source/Code_Style.md`

If there is any conflict, follow `Code_Style.md`.

## Required Naming Conventions

- Config parameter: `<Ma><Pn>` (CamelCase), for example `SecOCSecuredTxPduLength`
- Config container type: `<Ma>_<Tn>Type`
- Enum type: `<Ma>_<Tn>_Type`
- Enum literals and `#define`: `<MIP>_<SN>` (uppercase, underscore-separated)
- Error defines: `<MIP>_E_<EN>` (uppercase)
- Global variable: `<Mip>_<Vn>` (in implementation source files)
- Non-config typedef: `<Ma>_<Tn>Type`
- Callouts: section macros and prototype style exactly as in `Code_Style.md`

## Enforcement Checklist

Before edits:

1. Determine the module prefix pair (`SecOC` / `SECOC` style).
2. Name new symbols with AUTOSAR patterns above.

After edits:

1. Re-check naming of new/changed symbols.
2. Ensure constants/enums/macros remain uppercase style.
3. Use `const` for read-only globals.
4. Avoid renaming public APIs unless explicitly requested.
